From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Pin HTTP/2 SETTINGS to Chrome's exact wire format

Detection vector: HTTP/2 fingerprinting reads the SETTINGS frame
parameters (order, values, and initial WINDOW_UPDATE), the HEADERS
frame pseudo-header order, and the priority frame pattern. Each
HTTP/2 client library has a unique SETTINGS fingerprint. Chromium's
default differs from Chrome stable in subtle ways.

This patch overrides the HTTP/2 session to send Chrome 138's exact
SETTINGS frame: HEADER_TABLE_SIZE=65536, ENABLE_PUSH=0,
INITIAL_WINDOW_SIZE=6291456, MAX_HEADER_LIST_SIZE=262144.

Surface: network-h2
Closes: HTTP/2 SETTINGS fingerprinting (Akamai h2 fingerprint)

--- a/net/spdy/spdy_session.cc
+++ b/net/spdy/spdy_session.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void SpdySession::SendInitialSettings() {
+  // AgenticBrowser: send Chrome 138's exact SETTINGS frame.
+  // Order matters for fingerprinting: HEADER_TABLE_SIZE, ENABLE_PUSH,
+  // INITIAL_WINDOW_SIZE, MAX_HEADER_LIST_SIZE.
+  const uint32_t kABSettings[] = {
+    {SETTINGS_HEADER_TABLE_SIZE, 65536},
+    {SETTINGS_ENABLE_PUSH, 0},
+    {SETTINGS_INITIAL_WINDOW_SIZE, 6291456},
+    {SETTINGS_MAX_HEADER_LIST_SIZE, 262144},
+  };
+  for (const auto& [id, val] : kABSettings) {
+    settings_map[id] = val;
+  }

--- a/net/spdy/spdy_session.cc
+++ b/net/spdy/spdy_session.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void SpdySession::SendInitialSettings() {
+  // AgenticBrowser: send initial WINDOW_UPDATE on stream 0 to
+  // match Chrome's connection-level window of 6291456.
+  SendWindowUpdate(0, 6291456 - kInitialWindowSize);
